{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/hoffmanlab/segway/pullrequests/39/comments/15607920.json"}, "code": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/hoffmanlab/segway/diff/hoffmanlab/segway:13bb4ad4f082..254d91f1be69?path=segway%2Frun.py"}, "html": {"href": "#!/hoffmanlab/segway/pull-requests/39/_/diff#comment-15607920"}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 39, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/hoffmanlab/segway/pullrequests/39.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/hoffmanlab/segway/pull-requests/39"}}, "title": "Optparse to argparse refactor"}, "content": {"raw": "This is all a bit confusing. How about:\n\n1) rename the argument to this to be `argv` instead of `args` so we stop reusing it to mean different things\n\nThen:\n\n```\n#!python\n\noptions = parser.parse_args(argv)\nargs = options.args\n```\n\nIs it necessary to `del options.args` afterwards? Because it looks like it is not.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>This is all a bit confusing. How about:</p>\n<p>1) rename the argument to this to be <code>argv</code> instead of <code>args</code> so we stop reusing it to mean different things</p>\n<p>Then:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite language-python\"><pre><span></span><span class=\"n\">options</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">parser</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">parse_args</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">argv</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">args</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">options</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">args</span>\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>Is it necessary to <code>del options.args</code> afterwards? Because it looks like it is not.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2016-03-10T19:54:40.615697+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Michael Hoffman", "uuid": "{ffa8e039-5d4d-4f69-a4ba-ac25cbaf700b}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bffa8e039-5d4d-4f69-a4ba